17 July 2013As part of promoting a spirit of volunteerism and observing the Nelson Mandela Day, Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) will tomorrow lend a helping hand to two orphanage homes in Atteridgeville, Pretoria. These are:Services to be rendered include delivery of donated groceries, cleaning of the premises, gardening, laundry, and general maintenance. GCIS will also donate computers to the homes. Members of the media are invited to cover the event. The details are:Date: 18 July 2013 Time: 09h00-14h00 Venue: 999 Mofokeng Street (Leamogetswe Safety Home), 64 Masopha Street (Kingdom Life Children s Centre)Enquiries: Nebo Legoabe, Deputy CEO: Intergovernmental Coordination and Stakeholder Management Cell: 0824532874For RSVP and interview requests contact Bongiwe Gambu 0827149463Issued by: Government Communication and Information System